TSDR Plugin for RTL-SDR using Soapy SDR API

This plugin provides support for RTL-SDR devices through the Soapy SDR abstraction layer.

Requirements:
- SoapySDR library (https://github.com/pothosware/SoapySDR)
- SoapyRTLSDR module (https://github.com/pothosware/SoapyRTLSDR)

Installation:
1. Install SoapySDR and the RTL-SDR module
2. Build this plugin by running 'make' in this directory
3. Copy the built library to the appropriate plugin directory

Parameters:
The plugin accepts parameters in the format "key1=value1,key2=value2"

Supported parameters:
- serial: RTL-SDR serial number (optional, uses first available if not specified)
- device: Specific device identifier (optional)

Example usage:
driver=rtlsdr,serial=12345678

Default settings:
- Sample rate: 3.2 MHz
- Frequency: 400 MHz
- Gain: Auto (normalized 0.0-1.0)
